# Dice Roller

Command-line dice rolling simulator built using Python.

## Overview

This project allows users to simulate rolling one or more dice with a customizable number of sides. The program generates random dice rolls, displays the results, and allows the user to continue rolling until they choose to quit.

## Project Files

- [View Dice Roller Source Code](./Dice_Roller.py)

## Features

- User-defined number of dice
- User-defined number of sides
- Random dice roll generation
- Replay functionality
- Command-line interaction

